@Vcondry84 I try and aim for long term capital gains tax if the catalyst is far enough (eg. Photonics). 

For example I’m sitting on unrealized ~450% return one of my $AXTI positions. 

But if there’s a major event like Greenland peace deal that would hurt your defense longs like $ONDS if you had it. Then just taking short term capital gains on like a 80% return is probably better than round tripping to breakeven then paying no tax on that
